defaultDecentralisation (question 16)defaultClive Betts asked for an annual report on departmental progress on decentralisation.
defaultAs I set out in my letter to the Committee on 6 June, we do not intend to produce a separate annual report as I am satisfied that there is already sufficient reporting. The Open Public Services Team under Oliver 
defaultLetwin
default and David Laws are publishing annual reports on the Open Public Services White Paper, including what has been done on decentralisation. Departments will also continue to report against their structural reform plans.
defaultThe Government continues to make great steps to decentralise power and money. For example, the Spending Round underlined our commitment to the devolution of economic powers from central 
defaultgovernment to local areas, bringing at least £20 billion under the strategic influence of Local Enterprise Partnerships in the years to 2021.
