defaultMargaret Hodge also asked about MPA oversight of Department for Education programmes. The £2.5 billion Priority School Building
default Programme is our major capital
default investment programme to rebuild dilapidated schools. It falls within the ambit of the MPA. I know the Education Funding Authority has welcomed the support and advice of MPA, including the leadership training that MPA has supported. The Programme is delivering ahead of schedule and securing savings of some 40 per cent on the capital costs
default of the previous Administration’
defaults programme.
defaultG4S —default Serious Fraud Office report (question 33)defaultKeith 
defaultVaz
default raised the issue of Government contracts with G4S, and asked about the timetable for the Serious Fraud Office (SFO) reporting its findings to the Ministry of Justice.
defaultThe timescale on when the SFO will report back to the Ministry of Justice is a matter for the SFO to consider independently of Government. Chris Grayling has committed to keep Parliament informed as and when he is able to do so.
defaultWe are clear that new business can only be awarded where the integrity of the contracts and the conduct of suppliers can be assured. Work continues on the independent audit of every Ministry of Justice contract with Serco and G4S, announced by Chris Grayling in July, and on the wider review announced by Francis Maude of all contracts held by Serco and G4S across Government. Serco also agreed in August to undertake a process of corporate renewal, which will be subject to an assessment by a Government committee, including non-executive directors, at the end of November.
defaultForensic Science Service (question 36)defaultAndrew Miller asked about a strategy for forensic sciences across Government.
defaultThe Forensi
defaultc Policy Group was established in 2012 in order to ensure a joined-up approach on the key issues on forensic science. It includes representatives from the Police, Crown. Prosecution Service, Ministry of Justice, the Department of Health, the Home Office, and the Ministry of Defence.
defaultThe provision of forensic services through a commercial market is working. As I said during my appearance, the Forensic Science Service was allowed to maintain a cost base that was far too high under the previous Government. As a result, the company was unable to compete with its commercial rivals, and was making heavy losses. The current commercial providers meet exactly the same quality 
defaultstandards as the Forensic Science Service did, but do not require public funding of £2 million a month.
defaultThe Government will respond in more detail on our approach to forensic science later this month in our response to the S
defaultcience and Technology Committee’
defaults inquiry.
defaultExpertise and Skills (question 59)defaultClive Betts asked about the skills and expertise in the Treasury to deliver infrastructure guarantees and the Help to Buy scheme.
defaultAs the Chancellor set out in the Budget, to drive forward infrastructure delivery we need the best people for the job. Infrastructure UK was set up in 2010 as a unit within
default the Treasury to work on the UK’
defaults long-term infrastructure priorities and secure private sector investment. It is largely staffed by commercial and finance professionals who have been recruited from top private sector companies.
defaultInfrastructure UK’
defaults staff includes a team of ten infrastr
defaultucture finance specialists with 
defaultbetween 8 and 26 years of experience in financing complex projects in the UK and abroad. These commercial and delivery experts and finance professionals have proven track records.
defaultThe Treasury has developed Help to Buy, in close co-operation with industry and regulators, to ensure that the scheme received the right technical input. In addition, the Treasury procured specialist advice from a major accountancy firm to determine the correct commercial scheme.
defaultThe Government has also appointed UK Asset Resolution (UKAR) to take responsibility for the day-to-day administration of Help to Buy on behalf of the Treasury. UKAR is a Government-owned entity managed by financial experts with a strong understanding of the UK mortgage market, especially in modelling and managing risk.
defaultThe organisation was established to manage the wind-down of the mortgage books of Northern Rock and Bradford &amp; Bingley and has demonstrated continued good management of this task.
